id: pm-wtq6
title: Strict skipped-test policy and linked-test assertion semantics
description: Introduce additive fail-on-skipped policy and assertion metadata for linked tests so successful exit codes alone are not the only verification signal.
type: Feature
status: closed
priority: 1
tags[4]: assertions,external-audit,linked-tests,pm-cli
created_at: "2026-04-04T12:42:41.897Z"
updated_at: "2026-04-04T14:02:57.886Z"
deadline: "2026-04-14T12:42:41.897Z"
author: codex-agent
estimated_minutes: 300
acceptance_criteria: pm test and pm test-all support fail-on-skipped policy; linked tests can define assertions (text/regex/json-threshold style) that fail deterministically when unmet.
parent: pm-5z9r
reviewer: maintainer-review
risk: medium
confidence: high
sprint: external-audit-followup
release: vnext
reporter: codex-agent
severity: medium
environment: linux-node25-local
repro_steps: Linked command exits 0 with logically bad output or skipped entries and still reports pass today.
resolution: Implemented strict skipped-policy and assertion semantics via pm-au2z.
expected_result: Verification can enforce assertion intent and optionally fail on skipped coverage.
actual_result: Exit-code-only semantics can overstate linked-test evidence quality.
affected_version: 2026.3.12
fixed_version: target-vnext
component: linked-test-runtime
regression: true
customer_impact: Improves confidence in governance automation and release-readiness evidence.
comments[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-04-04T12:42:41.897Z",codex-agent,"Duplicate-check evidence: pm-4g5i classifies failures but does not add fail-on-skipped policy or user-defined assertion evaluation semantics."
  "2026-04-04T14:02:29.955Z",codex-agent,Child task pm-au2z delivered fail-on-skipped policy and assertion semantics with coverage gate passing.
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-04-04T12:42:41.897Z",codex-agent,"Compatibility guard: default behavior unchanged unless new policy/assertion options are used."
close_reason: Strict skipped-policy and assertion semantics feature completed additively with full regression evidence.
body: Implements unresolved external report #4 plus strict governance option from report #1 improvements.
